<br>
Anyway, a Japanese restaurant near me when I lived in Sao Paulo served what they called a 'tropical caiprinha'.  I don't know exactly what was in it, but it was absolutely the yummiest drink I ever tasted.  The alcohol in it was sake, and the fruit was crushed strawberries and kiwi fruit (possibly other stuff I couldn't identify), and ice.  I doubt there was anything diluting the sake either, except the fruit juice and the ice.  It was strooonggg... two of these and wow! yet it went down like fruit juice.  That was definitely the best mixed drink I have ever tasted *drools at the memory*.  The Japanese food was mediocre, I used to keep going back for the drinks. =)  I've tried experimenting a bit to see if I can recreate it, but I just can't get it as good as the original.  :( <p><table border=0><tr><td width=20%><img src="http://users.bigpond.net.au/stbt/didi/a_didisig.gif" height=120 width=120></td><td><FONT FACE="Tempus Sans ITC" SIZE="2">
